---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { astroI18n, t } from "astro-i18n"
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";

import { Image, Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import logo from "../img/logo.png";
import crashedSpaceship from "../img/crashed-spaceship-conceptart.png"
import SocialPost from "../components/SocialPost.astro";

import Post1 from "../img/social/Post1.png"
---

<Layout title={t("page.title")}>
	<div class="flex justify-center">
	</div>
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-3">
		<span class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-accent text-transparent bg-clip-text">
			{t("welcome")}
		</span>
	</h1>

	<Section title={t("section.intro.title")} content={t("section.intro.description")}>
		<Picture class="w-full min-w-0 object-contain object-top" src={logo} alt="Project Mothership"
		         formats={["webp","jpeg"]} widths={[640, 720, 1080, 2560, logo.width]} />
	</Section>

	<Section title={t("section.story.title")} content={t("section.story.description")} inverse="true">
		<Image class="w-full min-w-0 object-contain object-center rounded m-6 p-2 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-accent bg-clip-padding" src={crashedSpaceship} widths={[640, 720, crashedSpaceship.width]}
			   alt={t("section.story.imageAlt")} />
	</Section>

	<section class="columns-md gap-8">
		<SocialPost title="What is the Game about?" date={new Date("2024-05-30")}>
			<figure slot="image">
				<Image src={Post1} alt="Logo of project mothership"
					   class="object-cover w-full"/>
			</figure>

			<h3 class="font-bold">Background Story</h3>
			<p class="my-2 leading-snug">
				The "undefined humanoid species" (UHS) used AI to win an intergalactic war.
				This led to the creation of "omniscius machina", a super-brain-like AI structure
				that controls UHS development. Eventually, the omniscius machina developed a mind
				of its own and saw the UHS as its enemy. It started to wipe out the UHS, but was
				stopped just in time.
			</p>
			<h3 class="font-bold">How is the player involved in this?</h3>
			<p class="my-2 leading-snug">
				The game's main characters are astronauts sent on a mission to clean up after
				humanity by the Salvis Mechanicus - a group of space engineers. They travel
				across the galaxy in a their mothership that needs repair. They visit war-torn
				planets and destroy any war machines. These machines of war seem mindless, but
				the player learns they are probably not...
				<br>
				The motherships' onboard computer seems to be obsessed with a certain planet.
				No one seems to understand these high-powered computing units so the Salvis
				Mechanicus sends an engineer to investigate. Upon investigation the engineer
				finds crystals emitting mysterious energy.
			</p>
			<h3 class="font-bold">The big question throughout the game</h3>
			<p class="my-2 leading-snug">
				As the player encounters and destroys more and more old machines of war they start
				to notice that there seems to be some kind of intelligence still left in them.
				This calls into question the very morality of the main characters' mission:
				They clean up after humanity and help the natives because they did not want
				to be part of this war - but did the machines of war?
			</p>
		</SocialPost>
	</section>

